        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "In the site-Bs and the site-Es of the model d- 3, the distinguished amino acids are 3-H, 11-D, 14-S and 20-C. The first three amino acids correspond to the active sites of trypsin, 40-H, 84-D and 177-S, respectively. Thus, such a series of study provided conclusive proof that the DEV model is a useful tool to predict the active sites of typsin.",
